# =============================================================================
# HELPFUL REMINDERS
# =============================================================================

# Files that SHOULD be committed (for reference):
# - .env.template (template with no real credentials)
# - .gitignore (this file)
# - README.md
# - requirements.txt
# - validate_structure.py (project validation script)
# - sql/scripts.sql
# - sql/data_generation.sql
# - python/generate_data.py
# - python/databricks_connector.py
# - python/simple_connection_test.py
# - python/setup.py
# - python/__init__.py
# - docs/README-overview.md

# Files that should NEVER be committed:
# - .env (contains real credentials)
# - Any file with actual passwords, tokens, or API keys
# - Large data files
# - Personal configuration files
# - IDE-specific settings with personal preferences
